      <h1 class="h4 mb-3">3. Enhance forms with the same target model</h1>
      <div class="tutorial-content mb-4">
        <p>Forms use the same pane-targeting rule.</p>
        <p>HET respects normal form behavior:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>native <code>method</code> and <code>action</code> defaults</li>
          <li>submitter overrides such as <code>formaction</code> and <code>formmethod</code></li>
          <li>submitter name/value pairs</li>
          <li><code>GET</code> query strings and standard non-<code>GET</code> form encodings</li>
        </ul>
        <p>You can also override the form's target from the clicked submit button:</p>
        <p>Relevant reference:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><a href="reference/requests#forms">Forms</a></li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <form method="post" action="/preview" target="tutorial-preview" data-tutorial-form>
        <input type="hidden" name="html" data-editor-output="html">
        <input type="hidden" name="js" data-editor-output="js">
        <input type="hidden" name="css" data-editor-output="css">

        <div class="mb-3">
          <label class="form-label fw-semibold" for="html-source">HTML</label>
          <textarea id="html-source" class="d-none" data-editor="html">&lt;main het-pane="main">
  &lt;form method="get" action="/search" het-target="main">
    &lt;label>
      Search
      &lt;input name="q">
    &lt;/label>
    &lt;button type="submit">Search&lt;/button>
  &lt;/form>
&lt;/main></textarea>
          <div class="editor-host" data-editor-host="html"></div>
        </div>

